member.summary:
Build + parse {scheme}://album/{id}[?quality={q}] placeholder URIs.
Every streaming plugin emits an album-download URI as the ReleaseInfo.DownloadUrl when an indexer returns a release. The download client later parses that URL back to recover the album id (and optionally a quality hint) so it can call the streaming-service API. This helper keeps the grammar + parse round-trip in one place — siblings of (search URLs) and (release GUID grammar).
Supported parse formats (parser is liberal so legacy releases continue to resolve after a plugin migrates):
New: {scheme}://album/{id}?quality={q}
New (no quality): {scheme}://album/{id}
Legacy path-segment quality: {scheme}://album/{id}/{q}
The emitter always uses the NEW format (?quality= query parameter). Legacy parsing exists only to drain in-flight downloads queued before a plugin migration.
Originally implemented in qobuzarr/src/Download/Services/AlbumIdExtractor.ExtractAlbumIdFromDownloadUrl. Lifted as Wave 19B so the apple/tidalarr download clients can adopt the same parser when their respective release-URL handling consolidates.

Toggle for an [Explicit] bracket inserted between 
and the format bracket. When true, the literal [Explicit] string is appended;
when false the bracket is omitted.

Toggle for a [LIVE] bracket inserted between 
and the format bracket. When true, the literal [LIVE] string is appended;
when false the bracket is omitted.

remarks.para:
This is a generic sibling of . The non-generic type continues to be the
on-disk/in-memory cache record used by ;
the generic version exists so callers can receive a parsed DTO without re-deserializing the body.

member.remarks:
File schema:

{
  "profiles": {
    "search":   { "maxRetries": 6, "retryBudget": "00:01:00", ... },
    "download": { "maxRetries": 3, ... }
  }
}

Reload is debounced for 150 ms after any FileSystemWatcher event so a
single editor save (which often produces a flurry of Created/Changed/Renamed
events) results in one re-read.

remarks.para:
Usage: message_start.message.usage usually carries the input token count;
message_delta.usage typically carries the final output_tokens. Both are folded
into a single  on the terminal chunk.

member.remarks:
Typical usage in an overridden Test(List<ValidationFailure> failures):

var builder = new TestValidationBuilder()
    .RequireNonEmpty("ConfigPath", Settings.ConfigPath,
        "Config path is required.")
    .RequireNonEmpty("DownloadPath", Settings.DownloadPath,
        "Download path is required.");

failures.AddRange(builder.Build());
if (builder.HasFailures) return;

// smoke HTTP call here …

member.summary:
true if any failures have been accumulated so far.
Use this to decide whether to skip the smoke HTTP call:

if (builder.HasFailures) return;
